<br>
Hunting in KC for 3 hours on Saturday.  I was the only warrior in group.  I managed to pull a Caller of Sathir back to the left moat, and we killed the mob...  Lo and behold, the first ever cobalt drop I'd ever seen here...  Couple ppl in group started to congratulate me.  But the leader of the group who was MLing for us, looted the warrior only cobalt boots.  He said we needed to roll for them.  I pointed out they were warrior only, and I was the only warrior in the group.  Didn't seem to matter to him, he said to roll.  A cleric ended up winning the roll for the boots, and walked away happy with something she couldn't even use.<br>
<br>
