 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/utreeslover.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Treeslover</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 315<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/10/01 1:36:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NBG Dead?</span><hr size=1> One of the reasons that NBG was so prevalent in the &quot;Old days&quot; (laf) was that almost every high level (read as anyone 50+) knew pretty much every other high level.  Pickup groups were considered grabbing from a group of individuals whom you may not be guilded with, but that you've certainly xp'd with from time to time over the course of levelling.<br>
<br>
